('Warfarin', 'Venous thrombosis, pulmonary embolism, atrial fibrillation with embolisation.', 'Hypersensitivity. Haemorrhagic tendencies or blood dyscrasias, recent surgery. Hepatic or renal impairment. Peptic ulcer, severe hypertension, bacterial endocarditis. psychosis, aneurysms, pericarditis, pericardial effusion, eclampsia, pre-eclampsia, threatened abortion, alcoholism. Cerebrovascular haemorrhage. Pregnancy and lactation.', 'Hypersensitivity, rash, alopecia, diarrhoea, drop in haematocrit, purple toes syndrome, skin necrosis, jaundice, nausea, vomiting, hepatic dysfunction, pancreatitis, increased LFT. Haemorrhage (narrow therapeutic index).'),
