('Zanamivir', 'Treatment and prophylaxis of influenza caused by influenza A and B viruses including swing flu. It is inhaled twice a day for five days through Diskhaler', 'Hypersensitivity. Chronic bronchitis, asthma or chronic obstructive lung disease.', 'Dizziness, irritation of the nose and joint pain.  Precipitation and/or exacerbation of bronchospasm. Allergic reactions.'),
('Zidovudine', 'Asymptomatic and symptomatic HIV disease. Prophylaxis of maternal-foetal HIV transmission. Prophylaxis of HIV infection in neonates.', 'Hypersensitivity.  Lactation.  Neutropenia.', 'Anorexia, myalgia, insomnia, nausea, rash, abdominal pain, fever, anaemia, neutropenia, leucopenia. Dizziness, taste perversion, convulsions, myopathy, nail, skin and oral mucosa pigmentation, pancreatitis, fat redistribution. Lactic acidosis, severe hepatomegaly. Blood dyscrasias.'),
