('Zoledronic Acid', 'Hypercalcemia of malignancy. Multiple myeloma. Bone metastases from solid tumors. Pagets disease. Osteoporosis in postmenopausal women.', 'Hypersensitivity.  Severe renal impairment. Pregnancy, lactation and children.', 'Common: Pancytopenia, confusion, nausea, flu like syndrome, fatigue, arthalgia, bradycardia, fever, thirst, renal impairment, taste perversion, electrolyte disturbances. Uncommon: Thrombocytopenia, conjunctivitis, vomiting, skeletal pain, chest pain, hypophosphataemia, hypomagnesiumia, headache, pruritus, rash.  Rare: Local reactions at infusion site. Asthenia, peripheral oedema, hypertension, bradycardia. Very Rare: Acute renal failure.'),
